    "overview_title": "Half Turns and Quarter Turns",
    "overview_subtitle": "Rotations of Figures on the Coordinate Plane",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students use patty paper to explore rotations of various figures on a coordinate plane. They then generalize about the effects that rotating a figure about the origin has on its coordinates. Students verify that two figures are congruent by specifying a sequence of rigid motions that map one figure onto another."
  },
